  "severity": "Important",
  "description": "Ruby is an extensible, interpreted, object-oriented, scripting language. It has features to process text files and to perform system management tasks.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* ruby/json: Ruby JSON: Denial of Service or Information Disclosure via format string injection (CVE-2026-33210)\n\n* erb: ERB: Arbitrary code execution via deserialization bypass (CVE-2026-41316)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.",
